tml#QColor) color.\r\n\r\nIssueForNewDevelopers", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In the  GUI library, we are using <code>QColor</code> quite often. It would be nice to start using more of <code>common::Color</code> instead. </p>\n<p>One of the features of <code>QColor</code> which we make use of and don't have in <code>common::Color</code> yet is the idea of an <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/qcolor.html#QColor\" rel=\"nofollow\">\"invalid\"</a> color.</p>\n<p>IssueForNewDevelopers</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2015-12-17T19:28:56.961161+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:23:41.477011+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 1809}